avoid InternalFailure you can create std::runtime exception with the error message, which the caller can catch using 
catch(std::exception& ex)
{
   print ex.what();
   elog<InternalFailure);
}

this way the caller can print the error message where it is invoked, assuming if there are multiple places this captureDump method is invoked we will have the message in those caller methods.

